    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-01-22T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-01-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="776"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d776">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.6581/5: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Legation in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Peck</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-01-22T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 22, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 22—7:26 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7. An unofficial but apparently entirely reliable report has been received that
                    the Chinese Government has almost completed a scheme for a government sugar
                    monopoly and that it will be announced in the near future.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Legation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Peck</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
